## 1. What is Node.js?

Node.js is **JavaScript that runs on your computer/server — not in the browser.**

It takes the same V8 engine Chrome uses and puts it on your machine so you can run JS anywhere.

| Browser JS | Node.js |
|---|---|
| ❌ Read/write files | ✅ Read/write files |
| ❌ Access database | ✅ Access database |
| ❌ Hide secret keys | ✅ Keep API keys secret |
| ❌ Be a server | ✅ BE the server |

