## 28. Posts Route with Ownership Checks

Your `posts` route protects create/update/delete with authentication.

- `GET /posts` = public list of posts
- `GET /posts/:id` = public single post
- `POST /posts` = protected, creates a post with `author: req.user.id`
- `PUT /posts/:id` = protected and verifies the post author before editing
- `DELETE /posts/:id` = protected and verifies ownership before deleting

This is how you enforce that only the owner can change their own post.

